Former President, Olusegun Obasanjo has adviced president Muhammadu Buhari to sign the Africa free trade agreement now that he still has the chance. Obasanjo disclosed this while speaking during a presidential panel at the Africa CEO Forum in Cote d’Ivoire Obasanjo said the action of Buhari toward the Free Trade agreement was disappointing and adviced him to do append his signature before it becomes too late. Nigeria was absent when Forty-four African countries signed the historic free-trade zone agreement last week. “That President Buhari didn’t sign the free trade agreement in Kigali is disappointing; I hope he signs it before it is too late. “Egypt started the discussion on the formation of the Organisation of African Unity but didn’t conclude it and Nigeria took over. “Nigeria was also central to the discussion of the free trade agreement, but I am surprised that the country withdrew from signing.” he added Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook